choices.text:
to play dice with the locals to get some money on a Saturday night. Add some cigarettes, and a beer or two, mix in a little bit of Aku, the local hallucinogen made of yabbies from the streams, boil together a cheap meal, a little oil to infuse some heat, and simmer away from children on a low, well ventilated, hob. Add family, friends, headhunters, boomerangs, the occasional spear, rotten food, envy of your neighbors, rudeness, wild spirits, a local religion from doped out visions of headhunters and professors of the University of Montana, scramble, and then consume locally. Get engaged to a lovely girl at the weekend from the beached pig, grab some cheap beer, booze the local carribean flavoured Waka Waka with your friends, pickle it with the family, and then wait. Do this for an extended period of time until the event happens, twenty twelve, babies, weddings, dads, mums, near misses, vanishing kids, repulsion, envy, suicide by headhunting, theft, beer, failure, smoke, guilt, shame, frustration, happiness, approximation, car wrecks, hit and runs, babies, marriage, anger, long evenings, days in, confusion, Africa, Africa, Africa.

And the motherfucker’s not even back yet.
